    "raw": "Bring esp32s3-office up with local HTTP debug endpoints so we can talk to the\nboard without the DMZ.\n\n## Facts (start of work)\n\n- Device: esp32s3-office at 192.168.88.73:9000 (Jaguar identify OK)\n- SDK: v2.0.0-alpha.195; containers: jaguar + thermo-esp32s3 (M1 heartbeat only)\n- Serial shows only \"heartbeat esp32s3-office\"; port 5000 closed -- no /healthz /logs\n- manage zones office still stale picopi .60 data\n\n## Process\n\n1. Pull whatever Jaguar exposes (identify, firmware, containers, serial monitor).\n2. If that does not unlock the path, ship a VERY simplified onboard app:\n   no encryption, no packages if avoidable, but serving /healthz and /logs on :5000.\n3. Then add GPIO (INPUT_PULLUP / INPUT_PULLDOWN sample), sensor read, IR send.\n4. Exercise by sending commands directly to the device (not via DMZ).\n\nTimebox: until 2026-07-14 13:00 America/New_York."
  },
